properties.Name: SolarPanel

Columns.Name: SolarPanelId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Component.

Columns.Name: FixedTiltAngleDegrees
Columns.Description: The fixed tilt degree angle of the solar panel.

Columns.Name: SolarPanelWidthMm
Columns.Description: The width of the solar panel.

Columns.Name: SolarPanelLengthMm
Columns.Description: The length of the solar panel.

Columns.Name: ModelNumber
Columns.Description: The model of the solar panel.

Columns.Name: PeakPowerW
Columns.Description: The peak power of the solar panel in W.

Columns.Name: OptimalOperatingVoltage
Columns.Description: The optimal operating voltage of the solar panel.

Columns.Name: OptimalOperatingCurrentAmps
Columns.Description: The optimal operating current of the solar panel in A.

Columns.Name: ShortCircuitCurrentAmps
Columns.Description: The solar panel short-circuit current in A.

Columns.Name: OpenCircuitVoltageV
Columns.Description: The solar panel open-circuit voltage.

Columns.Name: MaximumSystemVoltageV
Columns.Description: The solar panel maximum system voltage.

Columns.Name: MinimumOperatingTemperatureC
Columns.Description: The solar panel minimum operating temperature  in C.

Columns.Name: MaximumOperatingTemperatureC
Columns.Description: The solar panel maximum operating temperature  in C.

Columns.Name: WarrantyPeriodMonths
Columns.Description: The warranty period in months.

Columns.Name: MountingStructureTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a mounting structure type.

Columns.Name: SolarPanelAirmassUnitsAm
Columns.Description: A unit of atmospheric mass measurement commonly used in discussion of rating solar photovoltaic panels. The AM measurement for photovoltaic solar panels at standard test conditions (STC) is 1.5AM.

Columns.Name: PhotovoltaicModuleConstructionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Photovoltaic Module Construction Type.

Columns.Name: ManufacturedByPartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.

Columns.Name: SolarArrayId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Component.

Columns.Name: SolarPanelWeightKg
Columns.Description: The solar panel weight in kg.

Columns.Name: AverageAnnualEnergyProductionKwh
Columns.Description: The total energy generated annually by a power station, on average over a period of time of full operation or since the start of full operation, measured in kilowatt-hours.

Columns.Name: MaximumSeriesFuseRatingA
Columns.Description: The maximum fuse rating in amps.

Columns.Name: NumberOfSolarCells
Columns.Description: The number of solar cells in the solar panel.

Columns.Name: CutoffVoltage
Columns.Description: The voltage levels (activation) at which the charge controller disconnects the photovoltaic array from the battery or the load from the battery.

Columns.Name: RatedPowerW
Columns.Description: The solar panels rated power expressed in watts.

Columns.Name: SolarCellTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a solar cell type.

Properties.Description:
A grouping of photovoltaic cells into the building block for solar panels.

Assemblies of photovoltaic cells are used to make solar modules which generate electrical power from sunlight.  Multiple cells in an integrated group, all oriented in one plane, constitute a solar photovoltaic panel or solar photovoltaic module.

The electrical energy generated from solar modules, referred to as solar power, is an example of solar energy. A group of connected solar modules (such as prior to installation on a pole-mounted tracker system) is called an "PV array."
